# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the user is
#   responsible for mapping their own environment. But for a self-contained application,
#   it may be handy to include them.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different environment, it may be
#   opt-in to ignore system dependencies.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#pdm.lock

